Data Scientist		Navinet		Boston, MA, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Position Summary<br /><br /></strong>NaviNet processes approximately one million healthcare network transactions per day, facilitating data flow among providers, payers and healthcare information exchanges. The Research Data Scientist will be part of a dynamic, fast-paced Product Research team and will explore approaches to modeling and analyzing data in both real-time and at-rest. Using these approaches the Research Data Scientist will develop predictive techniques using statistics and machine learning, and will recommend tools for steering network activity toward beneficial outcomes. The Research Data Scientist will present methods and findings in actionable layman’s terms, including visualizations, to a wide variety of stakeholders including developers and senior executives.<br /><br /><strong>ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:</strong>  (in order to be considered for this position, the individual must be able to perform essential functions listed below): <br /><ul><ul><li>Model real-time and at-rest network data in order to enable analysis</li> <li>Design and implement data extraction, transformation, aggregation and manipulation functions to prepare data for analysis</li> <li>Design and implement algorithms to analyze, predict and prescribe network behavior using mathematical, statistical and machine learning techniques</li> <li>Combine multiple data sources both internal and external as appropriate for techniques employed</li> <li>Discover patterns, trends, risks and anomalies in the data; draw inferences and conclusions</li> <li>Present techniques, results and findings to a wide variety of stakeholders both technical and non-technical</li> <li>Create compelling visualizations of network data, activity and behavior</li> <li>Work with Product Development to add actionable techniques and results to the product roadmap and to Business Intelligence tool sets</li> <li>Provide thought leadership within the company and externally around data science, analytics, machine learning and prescriptive techniques with respect to the healthcare industry</li> <li>All other duties as assigned</li> <br /></ul></ul>To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential function listed above satisfactorily.  Reasonable accommodations may be made in certain circumstances to enable individuals with qualified disabilities to perform the essential functions.  <br /><br /><strong>REQUIREMENTS:<br /> <br /></strong><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Mathematics, Statistics or Computer Science; Master’s Degree or PhD a plus</li> <li>Minimum of 2 years relevant working experience in Data Science, or equivalent work-study experience</li> <li>Expertise in R or Matlab, or with Python data science libraries</li> <li>Highly skilled in formal scientific and mathematical methods</li> <li>Highly skilled in statistic, stochastic and linear algebra tools and methods</li> <li>Experience with predictive analysis and machine learning</li> <li>Programming skills in at least 1 high level language such as C#, Java, Node.js, Python, C or C++</li> <li>Familiarity or experience working with cloud and elastic compute environments such as AWS</li> <li>Experience with graph and social network analysis is a strong plus</li> <li>Experience with data definition and manipulation languages such as SQL is a strong plus</li> <li>Experience with “NoSQL” data stores such as graph or document databases is a plus</li> <li>Experience with structured data formats such as JSON or XML is a plus</li> <li>Healthcare industry experience is a plus</li> <li>Software development or architecture experience is a plus</li> <li>Experience using a Unix/Linux operating system is a plus</li> <li>Experience with deep learning is a plus</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Qualifications<br /></strong><ul><li>Excellent oral and written communication skills</li> <li>Fluent with a wide variety of analytic, stochastic and statistical mathematical concepts</li> <li>Good understanding of the problems to which such concepts can be applied</li> <li>Works well in a highly dynamic and collaborative environment</li> <li>Highly creative and able to adjust approach as new information is uncovered</li> <li>Self-motivated, exploratory and high level of curiosity to continually move to next steps and push the state-of-the-art</li> <br /><br /></ul>NaviNet is committed to providing equal employment opportunity (EEO) to all persons, regardless of proscribed category as protected by local, state and federal regulations. This applies to hiring, tenure of employment, and all terms and conditions of employment. <br /><br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">NaviNet is America’s leading healthcare collaboration network. We connect over 40 health plans and 60% of the nation’s physicians, representing 420,000 clinical and administrative healthcare professionals. We help payers and providers boost care quality, lower costs, and improve population health management with NaviNet Open, our payer-provider collaboration platform. For more information, please visit www.NaviNet.net. Join us on Twitter @NaviNet</div>